						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Front side of the stone now used as door frame of the central shrine of the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.,</hi> records a gift of land and money. It refers to <hi rend="bold">Kailāsa-nṛipa</hi> and his son <hi rend="bold">Dhanasaṅgraha</hi> who are praised.</p>						

